{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2023-1212","published":"2023-04-11T11:05:08Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:18:51.933644Z","upstream":["CVE-2023-1380","CVE-2023-1513","CVE-2023-28328"],"summary":"kernel security update","details":"The Linux Kernel, the operating system core itself.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\n\nKernel: A denial of service issue in  az6027 driver in\ndrivers/media/usb/dev-usb/az6027.c(CVE-2023-28328)\r\n\r\nA slab-out-of-bound read problem was found in brcmf_get_assoc_ies in drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/cfg80211.c in the Linux Kernel. This issue could occur when assoc_info-&gt;req_len data is bigger than the size of the buffer, defined as WL_EXTRA_BUF_MAX, leading to a denial of service.(CVE-2023-1380)\r\n\r\nA flaw was found in KVM. When calling the KVM_GET_DEBUGREGS ioctl, on 32-bit systems, there might be some uninitialized portions of the kvm_debugregs structure that could be copied to userspace, causing an information leak.(CVE-2023-1513)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"kernel","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP3","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/kernel&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP3"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"4.19.90-2304.1.0.0196.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["python2-perf-4.19.90-2304.1.0.0196.oe1.aarch64.rpm","perf-debuginfo-4.19.90-2304.1.0.0196.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-debuginfo-4.19.90-2304.1.0.0196.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-source-4.19.90-2304.1.0.0196.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bpftool-debuginfo-4.19.90-2304.1.0.0196.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-tools-devel-4.19.90-2304.1.0.0196.oe1.aarch64.rpm","python3-perf-4.19.90-2304.1.0.0196.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-debugsource-4.19.90-2304.1.0.0196.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-4.19.90-2304.1.0.0196.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-tools-debuginfo-4.19.90-2304.1.0.0196.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bpftool-4.19.90-2304.1.0.0196.oe1.aarch64.rpm","python3-perf-debuginfo-4.19.90-2304.1.0.0196.oe1.aarch64.rpm","python2-perf-debuginfo-4.19.90-2304.1.0.0196.oe1.aarc